main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Mankato, Minnesota on July 10, 1964, involving an object traveling in a random erratic pattern.
interesting points: The sighting occurred at approximately 11:27 p.m., The object was observed visually for a duration of 5 minutes, There was only one object reported, The conclusion stated that the object then disappeared, NASA and the Air Force investigated the sighting, leading to findings that the object was possibly space debris.
witness description: a student at Mankato State College studying astronomy
